<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="497" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,724,1685]" pageId="1" pageNumber="497">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,904,929]" pageId="1" pageNumber="497">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species epithet comes from the Latin adjectives 
<emphasis box="[927,985,905,928]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="497">niger</emphasis>
, - 
<emphasis box="[1008,1033,905,928]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="497">ra</emphasis>
, - 
<emphasis box="[1056,1101,905,928]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="497">rum</emphasis>
, and 
<emphasis box="[1163,1231,904,928]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="497">alatus</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[1245,1268,905,928]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="497">-a</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[1282,1325,905,928]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="497">-um</emphasis>
, meaning “black” and “winged,” in reference to the black forewings of this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="497" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,724,1685]" pageId="1" pageNumber="497">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,976,1001]" pageId="1" pageNumber="497">Description.</emphasis>
Length of each male forewing 12.0 mm (n = 5); specimens in alcohol with head, thorax, and forewings black (
<figureCitation box="[346,414,1012,1037]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1122,1145]" captionTargetBox="[203,1436,237,1094]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,195,1098]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Male genitalia and forewing of Macrostemum nigralatum n. sp. 6, left lateral. 7, dorsal. 8, ventral. 9, phallus, left lateral. 10, phallus, ventral. 11, right forewing, dorsal. IX = segment IX, X = segment X, Inf = inferior appendage (paired), Lat = lateral lobe (paired), a Inf = apical segment of an inferior appendage (paired), b Inf = basal segment of an inferior appendage (paired)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610700/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="497">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,724,1685]" pageId="1" pageNumber="497">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[376,514,1048,1073]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1122,1145]" captionTargetBox="[203,1436,237,1094]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,195,1098]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Male genitalia and forewing of Macrostemum nigralatum n. sp. 6, left lateral. 7, dorsal. 8, ventral. 9, phallus, left lateral. 10, phallus, ventral. 11, right forewing, dorsal. IX = segment IX, X = segment X, Inf = inferior appendage (paired), Lat = lateral lobe (paired), a Inf = apical segment of an inferior appendage (paired), b Inf = basal segment of an inferior appendage (paired)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610700/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="497">Figures 1–5</figureCitation>
). In dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[713,782,1048,1073]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1122,1145]" captionTargetBox="[203,1436,237,1094]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,195,1098]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Male genitalia and forewing of Macrostemum nigralatum n. sp. 6, left lateral. 7, dorsal. 8, ventral. 9, phallus, left lateral. 10, phallus, ventral. 11, right forewing, dorsal. IX = segment IX, X = segment X, Inf = inferior appendage (paired), Lat = lateral lobe (paired), a Inf = apical segment of an inferior appendage (paired), b Inf = basal segment of an inferior appendage (paired)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610700/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="497">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
), segment IX rectangular with subrectangular incision for half of its length anteriorly; lateral lobes of segment IX subrectangular, truncate apically with long setae; in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[228,300,1120,1145]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1122,1145]" captionTargetBox="[203,1436,237,1094]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,195,1098]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Male genitalia and forewing of Macrostemum nigralatum n. sp. 6, left lateral. 7, dorsal. 8, ventral. 9, phallus, left lateral. 10, phallus, ventral. 11, right forewing, dorsal. IX = segment IX, X = segment X, Inf = inferior appendage (paired), Lat = lateral lobe (paired), a Inf = apical segment of an inferior appendage (paired), b Inf = basal segment of an inferior appendage (paired)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610700/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="497">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
), segment IX short with truncated lateral lobes, convex basodorsally, truncated apicoventrally, apicolateral margins with numerous setae; in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[829,898,1156,1181]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1122,1145]" captionTargetBox="[203,1436,237,1094]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,195,1098]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Male genitalia and forewing of Macrostemum nigralatum n. sp. 6, left lateral. 7, dorsal. 8, ventral. 9, phallus, left lateral. 10, phallus, ventral. 11, right forewing, dorsal. IX = segment IX, X = segment X, Inf = inferior appendage (paired), Lat = lateral lobe (paired), a Inf = apical segment of an inferior appendage (paired), b Inf = basal segment of an inferior appendage (paired)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610700/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="497">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
), segment IX subrectangular with anterolateral lobes and V-shaped incision posteromesally. Segment X in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[963,1032,1192,1217]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1122,1145]" captionTargetBox="[203,1436,237,1094]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,195,1098]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Male genitalia and forewing of Macrostemum nigralatum n. sp. 6, left lateral. 7, dorsal. 8, ventral. 9, phallus, left lateral. 10, phallus, ventral. 11, right forewing, dorsal. IX = segment IX, X = segment X, Inf = inferior appendage (paired), Lat = lateral lobe (paired), a Inf = apical segment of an inferior appendage (paired), b Inf = basal segment of an inferior appendage (paired)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610700/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="497">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
), long, with deep V-shaped incision apically forming 2 oval lobes; in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[737,810,1228,1253]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1122,1145]" captionTargetBox="[203,1436,237,1094]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,195,1098]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Male genitalia and forewing of Macrostemum nigralatum n. sp. 6, left lateral. 7, dorsal. 8, ventral. 9, phallus, left lateral. 10, phallus, ventral. 11, right forewing, dorsal. IX = segment IX, X = segment X, Inf = inferior appendage (paired), Lat = lateral lobe (paired), a Inf = apical segment of an inferior appendage (paired), b Inf = basal segment of an inferior appendage (paired)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610700/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="497">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) with somewhat triangular, round apically. Inferior appendages slender, long; each with basal segment slender, about 1.5 times as long as apical segment; apical segment slender with short setae apically, rounded apex; curving slightly mesad in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[1260,1331,1300,1325]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1122,1145]" captionTargetBox="[203,1436,237,1094]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,195,1098]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Male genitalia and forewing of Macrostemum nigralatum n. sp. 6, left lateral. 7, dorsal. 8, ventral. 9, phallus, left lateral. 10, phallus, ventral. 11, right forewing, dorsal. IX = segment IX, X = segment X, Inf = inferior appendage (paired), Lat = lateral lobe (paired), a Inf = apical segment of an inferior appendage (paired), b Inf = basal segment of an inferior appendage (paired)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610700/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="497">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Phallus axe-shaped, expanded basally, bulb-like subapically, pointed apically in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[1152,1226,1336,1361]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1122,1145]" captionTargetBox="[203,1436,237,1094]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,195,1098]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Male genitalia and forewing of Macrostemum nigralatum n. sp. 6, left lateral. 7, dorsal. 8, ventral. 9, phallus, left lateral. 10, phallus, ventral. 11, right forewing, dorsal. IX = segment IX, X = segment X, Inf = inferior appendage (paired), Lat = lateral lobe (paired), a Inf = apical segment of an inferior appendage (paired), b Inf = basal segment of an inferior appendage (paired)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610700/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="497">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
); long, hourglassshaped in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[419,487,1372,1397]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1122,1145]" captionTargetBox="[203,1436,237,1094]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,195,1098]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Male genitalia and forewing of Macrostemum nigralatum n. sp. 6, left lateral. 7, dorsal. 8, ventral. 9, phallus, left lateral. 10, phallus, ventral. 11, right forewing, dorsal. IX = segment IX, X = segment X, Inf = inferior appendage (paired), Lat = lateral lobe (paired), a Inf = apical segment of an inferior appendage (paired), b Inf = basal segment of an inferior appendage (paired)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610700/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="497">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="497" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,724,1685]" pageId="1" pageNumber="497">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1408,1433]" pageId="1" pageNumber="497">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The genitalia of the new species are similar to those of the well-known and widespread 
<taxonomicName authority="(Walker 1852)" authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1852" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1852" class="Insecta" family="Hydropsychidae" genus="Macrostemum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="497" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fastosum">
<emphasis box="[1300,1323,1409,1432]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="497">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1336,1436,1408,1432]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="497">fastosum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Walker, F." box="[158,306,1444,1469]" pageId="1" pageNumber="497" refId="ref2819" refString="Walker, F. (1852) Catalogue of specimens of neuropterous insects in the collection of the British Museum. Printed by order of the Trustees, London, 76 pp." type="book" year="1852">Walker 1852</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
found in Southeast Asia: Bali, Java, Sumatra, 
<collectingCountry box="[849,906,1445,1468]" name="Laos" pageId="1" pageNumber="497">Laos</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[919,1021,1444,1469]" name="Thailand" pageId="1" pageNumber="497">Thailand</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[1083,1178,1444,1469]" name="Vietnam" pageId="1" pageNumber="497">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Malicky, H." box="[1194,1359,1444,1469]" pageId="1" pageNumber="497" refId="ref2442" refString="Malicky, H. (2010) Atlas of Southeast Asian Trichoptera. Faculty of Science Printing Unit, Chiang Mai University, Chiang Mai Province, 346 pp." type="book" year="2010">Malicky 2010</bibRefCitation>
). They can separate by characteristics of the dorsal view of segment X. In 
<taxonomicName authority="Suwannarat &amp; Malicky &amp; Laudee, 2018" authorityName="Suwannarat &amp; Malicky &amp; Laudee" authorityYear="2018" box="[910,1201,1480,1504]" class="Insecta" family="Hydropsychidae" genus="Macrostemum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="497" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigralatum" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[910,1201,1480,1504]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="497">Macrostemum nigralatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1210,1273,1480,1505]" pageId="1" pageNumber="497">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1210,1273,1480,1505]" pageId="1" pageNumber="497" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, segment X is rectangular with a deep V-shaped incision apically forming 2 oval lobes, rounded apically. The dorsal view of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1852" class="Insecta" family="Hydropsychidae" genus="Macrostemum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="497" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fastosum">
<emphasis box="[1405,1428,1517,1540]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="497">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[151,251,1552,1576]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="497">fastosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
segment X has a V-shaped incision for 1/2 of its length, with apical lobes bent outward apically. They can be separated very easily by the color of the forewings, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1852" box="[773,912,1588,1612]" class="Insecta" family="Hydropsychidae" genus="Macrostemum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="497" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fastosum">
M. 
<emphasis box="[812,912,1588,1612]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="497">fastosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has yellow wings with dark markings, but the wings are black without marking in the new species (
<figureCitation box="[758,828,1624,1649]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1122,1145]" captionTargetBox="[203,1436,237,1094]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,195,1098]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Male genitalia and forewing of Macrostemum nigralatum n. sp. 6, left lateral. 7, dorsal. 8, ventral. 9, phallus, left lateral. 10, phallus, ventral. 11, right forewing, dorsal. IX = segment IX, X = segment X, Inf = inferior appendage (paired), Lat = lateral lobe (paired), a Inf = apical segment of an inferior appendage (paired), b Inf = basal segment of an inferior appendage (paired)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610700/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="497">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). The Brazilian species 
<taxonomicName box="[1102,1220,1625,1648]" class="Insecta" family="Hydropsychidae" genus="Macrostemum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="497" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrum">
<emphasis box="[1102,1125,1625,1648]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="497">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1140,1220,1625,1648]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="497">nigrum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation author="Franca, D. &amp; Paprocki, H. &amp; Calor, A. R." box="[1230,1436,1624,1648]" pageId="1" pageNumber="497" pagination="301 - 335" refId="ref2215" refString="Franca, D., Paprocki, H. &amp; Calor, A. R. (2013) The genus Macrostemum Kolenati 1859 (Trichoptera: Hydropsychidae) in the Neotropical Region: Description of two new species, taxonomic notes, distributional records and key to males. Zootaxa, 3716 (3), 301 - 335." type="journal article" year="2013">
<collectingCountry box="[1230,1306,1625,1648]" name="France" pageId="1" pageNumber="497">Franca</collectingCountry>
<emphasis box="[1314,1365,1624,1648]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="497">et al</emphasis>
. 2013
</bibRefCitation>
also has the forewings entirely black, but the male genitalia are different.
</paragraph>
